env name : TextSummarizer
package name : TextSummarizer

1. Create repo in github and add .gitignore, README.md and LICENSE file
2. Create template.py file and update code and run it
3. Push the files created to github 
4. Create virtual environment: 
   conda create -n TextSummarizer python=3.9 -y
5. Activate environment : conda activate TextSummarizer
6. Update requirements.txt (-e . will call for setup.py file and install the local package)
7. Write code for setup.py file so that it will install the local package
8. Run pip install -r requirements.txt
9. Writing code for logging in src/logging/__init__.py file
10. Write code for utils/common.py file
11. Build model in google colab and optimize the number of epochs for better performance
12. link for data: https://github.com/Wonders11/Summarizer-data/blob/main/summarizer-data.zip


